{"key":"processedPost-5756476","value":{"id":5756476,"first":5756360,"last":5756781,"when":1150466143,"utime":"06/16/06 04:55 PM","content":"You can hydrate cased substrates by putting them in the sink and letting the faucet fill up the tray so it slowly runs over the edges.  Place something on top of the substrate to keep it from floating if necessary.  A couple of jars of water will hold it down. Allow the faucet to gently run for a couple of hours, then drain and put back in the FC.  Add fresh casing material to replace any that washed off during the rinse-dunk.<br />RR","title":"Re: Casing questions"}}